<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00081</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PRESCRIBING A MANDATORY OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY, HEALTH, AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM FOR ALL ARTISTS IN THE FILM, TELEVISION, AND THEATER INDUSTRIES OF THE PHILIPPINES, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Prescribing A Mandatory Occupational Safety, Health, And Emergency Response Program For All Artists In The Film, Television, And Theater Industries Of The Philippines</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Prescribes a mandatory occupational safety, health, and emergency response program for all artists in the film, television, and theater industries of the Philippines in their workplace.  Ensures safety and establishes emergency protocols while artists are at work.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME :          “Artists’ Safety on Set (ASSET) Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ONG, RONNIE L., DELOS SANTOS, ALFRED C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Olivarez (000 2019-08-14)</td><td>2. Tan (S.A.) (000 2020-01-29)</td><tr><td>3. Nieto (000 2020-02-03)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>